European Stocks, U.S. Futures Drop as Moody's Downgrades Spain, Oil Climbs

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-10T08:04:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/european-stocks-u-s-futures-drop-as-moody-s-downgrades-spain-oil-climbs.html
European stocks declined as Moody’s
Investors Service cut  Spain ’s credit rating and violence in  Libya  continued to drive up oil prices. U.S. stock-index futures
and Asian shares slid.  Spain’s rating was downgraded to Aa2 by Moody’s. The
ratings company has a negative outlook on the country’s debt.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 0.6 percent to
279.62 at 8:03 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  